The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Profit leaps 72% to Rs 139 crore

 OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT 

 Mumbai, July 13: Associated Cement Companies (ACC) today reported a 72 per cent jump in first-quarter net profit at Rs 139.36 crore compared with Rs 81.23 crore in the same period last year.

 Net sales on a stand-alone basis shot up over 19 per cent to Rs 1128.25 crore from Rs 947.93 crore in the year-ago period. Total income stood at Rs 1169.76 crore, while other income was Rs 41.51 crore.

 On a stand-alone basis, the cement business generated revenues of Rs 981.39 crore. On a consolidated basis, the group posted a net profit after exceptional items of Rs 146.95 crore compared with Rs 86.78 crore same time last year. Total income increased to Rs 1,251.37 crore (Rs 1,059.10 crore).

 The company said the sale of cement for the period increased 13 per cent to 4.41 million tonnes compared with 3.89 million tonnes for the same period last year. Higher volumes and improved operating efficiency resulted in a higher profit before interest, depreciation and exceptional items. 

 The interest cost was up 5 per cent at Rs 21.92 crore and depreciation was higher at Rs 47.98 crore. This was on account of acquisition of Wadi captive power plant and commissioning of Chaibasis captive power plant and expansion of the Gagal unit. 




